title: Rebirth of Mothra (1996)
description:
Rebirth of Mothera (1996)
  Mosura (original title)

  104 min   -  Action | Fantasy | Sci-Fi

Rebirth of Mothra, released in Japan as Mothra (??? Mosura?), is the first in a trilogy of Kaiju films produced by Toho, in which 
Mothra's son saves the world from environment-threatening monsters. This film features the monsters Mothra, Mothra Leo, Fairy Mothra, 
Desghidorah (or Death-Ghidorah), and Garugaru. Rebirth of Mothra was the final Toho kaiju film with which long-time producer Tomoyuki 
Tanaka was directly involved (he died less than six months after its release).

A new Mothra takes to the air and must battle Death Ghidora to save humanity. 

Director:
 Okihiro Yoneda 

Writers:
 Masumi Suetani (screenplay), Tomoyuki Tanaka (creator) 

Stars:
 Megumi Kobayashi, Sayaka Yamaguchi, Aki Hano
